5:
All tourism-related requests have
been fulfilled. Objective completed.
My work here is done.
9:
We stopped by the restaurants on
my list, and I got the seasonings I
wanted... Talk about a fulfilling day.
14:
I am excited to taste your future
cooking.
18:
Thanks for showing us around, Sera.
It was fun!
23:
Gotta say, I never expected you to
be so good at this. Maybe I had you
pegged all wrong.
26:
Huh. So you're meant to take it slow
while sightseeing. You learn
something new every day.
29:
No way could we take more than a
day of your version of sightseeing.
Won't be forgetting that mad dash
for a LONG time.
33:
Sera, you did a superb job meeting
everyone's needs and making sure
we all had a great time.
42:
No. Everything is fine. Did you all
have a good time today? Was our
outing satisfactory?
46:
...Yes? That's what we were just
discussing.
50:
Is that so? Then I have
accomplished my objective. The
only matter left on the agenda is to
return.
55:
Sera, are you all right? You seem
bothered by something.
59:
I am not sure what it is. I feel as if I
forgot to do something, but I am
unsure what.
62:
Regardless, we are out of time
today. I suppose I should not think
too much about it.
65:
The day isn't completely over yet.
There's something I'd like to do
before we leave... Sera, would you
mind coming with me?
68:
I see you are already looking for
another adventure. Very well. I shall
indulge your curiosity.
74:
Oh... Looks like you're going to win
again! Guess I can't beat you when
it comes to driving, huh?
77:
I have not neglected my daily
training and calibrations, even
though I do not often ride a
motorcycle as of late.
80:
Ahaha, I lost. This was your first time
driving one of these, right? You're
really something else.
83:
At a high enough speed, the friction
of the water's surface becomes
similar to that of a motorcycle on
the road. Calculating the trajectory
of the waves is also easy.
86:
...Dez. You already rode a personal
watercraft yesterday.
90:
You also made sure everyone else is
waiting back on land. Why did you
bring me here alone?
93:
You caught me. Yeah, racing here
was just an excuse. I wanted to chat
about the past a little bit.
96:
The past? You mean when we lived
in our old world? It is strange for you
to be the one initiating a
conversation about it.
100:
Can you blame me? My memories
are more intact than yours. You
could say I remember more than I
want to.
102:
But... I still hold onto some. Back
when we used to hang out together...
104:
I remember one day we were off
duty and sat on a bench together.
Nothing special was going on in the
city around us.
106:
Then, as you were staring at the
passing traffic, you whispered, "Life
in this moment is... fun."
108:
The old you never said stuff like that,
so it was surprising.
111:
That seems... likely, though I do not
possess memories of such a
moment.
114:
Yeah, well... I guess my point is... I feel
the same now.
118:
I am afraid I do not comprehend
what you are trying to say.
121:
Guess I'll have to spell it out for you.
Earlier, you felt bothered, right? I bet
it's because you didn't want this trip
with your friends to end.
123:
That's how much you're living in the
moment and enjoying the present.
So there's no need to worry about
your missing memories anymore,
you know?
126: That is true. I already knew that.
129:
Or... I suppose I learned that right
now. It seems I was mistaken.
132:
Dez! I completely forgot about my
own wish for today.
136:
Though it is a bit late... We should
return to the others and fulfill it.
141:
Dez's little adventure was pretty
brutal... especially the part where we
went to the casino. Ugh...
144:
Ahaha, sorry about that. But I lost
too, so this might be the perfect
timing to use the phrase "I feel your
pain."
148:
As if. I was gonna win, but I was
stupid enough to let you goad me
into throwing.
152:
Dez is quite the troublemaker. An
awful personality trait, in my opinion.
157: The sun is halfway below the horizon.
162:
Yeah... This isn't our first time here,
but somehow it feels different than
usual.
167:
Sera, was watching the sunset here
your wish for today?
172:
Hehe... Commander, I have a
confession to make—I hold no
attachment to this place.
176:
What I wanted was to watch the
sunset with everyone. In other
words... Your presence is what
matters the most.
180:
I see. As long as you're happy, then I
am too.
184:
You've really softened up, Sera. I kind
of like this change.
187:
But the parts of you that haven't
changed are also nice. Well, with the
exception of your lack of humor.
191:
Was that an insult, Dez?! Explain
yourself this instant!
195: Yep... Girl can't take a joke.
199:
Ahaha, it feels like these two are
always going at it, huh?
204:
They look like they're enjoying
themselves.
209:
L-like I informed you before, I am not
boring! I have already studied the
art of humor and fully grasp it!
212:
Oh, yeah? Then prove it. Show me
you know how to have a good time!
216:
I have an ace up my sleeve! My
ninja friend in Starview Village
taught me a trick!
219:
For a moment like this... You need
fireworks!
